  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-11461">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 1. </span>
      Discuss the prevention of and treatment for the health concerns that could
      occur while backpacking, including hypothermia, heat reactions, frostbite,
      dehydration, insect stings, tick bites, snakebite, and blisters. <br /><i
        >Resources:</i
      >
      <a href="https://youtu.be/nxExCQiWa_U?si=E-FC1vbHZYI0vxhb" target="_blank"
        >Backpacking First Aid (What to Carry + Foot Care, Snakes, Poison
        Plants, Hypothermia, etc.) (video)</a
      ><br />
      <a href="https://youtu.be/lIvLRG31MZI?si=Y7vTYYNYNzcl_MV2" target="_blank"
        >Preventing and Treating Blisters (video)</a
      ><br />
      <a href="https://youtu.be/GHN8008brQw?si=MVUMbLRpSWLSkOZP" target="_blank"
        >Preventing and Treating Frostbite (video)</a
      >
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-11462">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 2. </span>
      Do the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11462 mb-requirement-id-11463">
        (a) List 10 items that are essential to be carried on any backpacking
        trek and explain why each item is necessary. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/J-Ae6OKjb6I?si=Ee6rn5JtoCrwtTFo"
          target="_blank"
          >What Are the 10 Essentials? (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11462 mb-requirement-id-11464">
        (b) Describe 10 ways you can limit the weight and bulk to be carried in
        your pack without jeopardizing your health or safety. <br /><i
          >Resource:</i
        >
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/Sg8-Urd6_JY?si=jti50ZHuKFyKyxNg"
          target="_blank"
        >
          10 FREE Ways to Reduce Base Weight Backpacking (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-11465">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 3. </span>
      Do the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11465 mb-requirement-id-11467">
        (a) Define limits on the number of backpackers appropriate for a trek
        crew. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a
          href="https://www.philmontscoutranch.org/treks/trekrequirements/crewrequirements/"
          target="_blank"
          >Philmont Crew Requirements (website)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://www.trailhiking.com.au/preparation/hiking-group-size/?srsltid=AfmBOooFYNMZTHANda2SBQWKHvaJuAW22YjziY4GhHYZ5vizsVquuu9D"
          target="_blank"
          >Ideal Hiking Group Size (website)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11465 mb-requirement-id-11468">
        (b) Describe how a trek crew should be organized. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://www.philmontscoutranch.org/treks/trek-resources/crew-positions/"
          target="_blank"
          >Crew Positions (website)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11465 mb-requirement-id-11469">
        (c) Tell how you would minimize risk on a backpacking trek.
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11465 mb-requirement-id-11470">
        (d) Explain the purpose of an emergency response plan. <br /><i
          >Resource:</i
        >
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/kypwGloorRk?si=EU5OPuV3A5yDbfx8"
          target="_blank"
          >Backpacking Emergency Response Plan (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-11466">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 4. </span>
      Do the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11466 mb-requirement-id-11471">
        (a) Describe the importance of following the Leave No Trace Seven
        Principles and the Outdoor Code while backpacking, and at least five
        ways you can lessen the crew's impact on the environment. <br /><i
          >Resource:</i
        >
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/Rpq01rO9ZR0?si=YIELlDJ5aYqUmUi9"
          target="_blank"
          >What is Leave No Trace? (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11466 mb-requirement-id-11472">
        (b) Describe proper methods of handling human and other wastes while on
        a backpacking trek. Describe the importance of and means to assure
        personal cleanliness while on a backpacking trek. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/Dk2k1QEyY7U?si=f4XaWPIgmh29_Cm9"
          target="_blank"
          >How to Poop in the Woods (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11466 mb-requirement-id-11473">
        (c) Tell what factors are important in choosing a campsite. <br /><i
          >Resource:</i
        >
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/dfpE0x6xTPU?si=op4Dp7UgoJk-qcNw"
          target="_blank"
          >How to Select a Campsite (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-11474">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 5. </span>
      Do the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11474 mb-requirement-id-11475">
        (a) Demonstrate two ways to treat water and tell why water treatment is
        essential. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/DIZz3iiZ2TY?si=krQx2K9GtsjHx1Lh"
          target="_blank"
          >The Best Way to Filter Water While Backpacking (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11474 mb-requirement-id-11476">
        (b) Explain to your counselor the importance of staying well-hydrated
        during a trek. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/zeZ--U2-Vz8?si=H86Y5a0Ac38NmuCb"
          target="_blank"
          >Hydrate! (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-11477">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 6. </span>
      Do the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11477 mb-requirement-id-11478">
        (a) Demonstrate that you can read topographic maps. <br /><i
          >Resource:</i
        >
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/CoVcRxza8nI?si=_vx1M7g51M2l_j4a"
          target="_blank"
          >How to Read a Topographic Map (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11477 mb-requirement-id-11479">
        (b) While on a trek, use a map and compass to establish your position on
        the ground at three different locations, OR use a GPS receiver to
        establish your position on a topographic map and on the ground at three
        different locations. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/0cF0ovA3FtY?si=o6nQlPuwNkbBJhwu"
          target="_blank"
          >How to Use a Compass (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11477 mb-requirement-id-11480">
        (c) Explain how to stay found, and what to do if you get lost. <br /><i
          >Resource:</i
        >
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/dq6fq-XdgUk?si=jzJ2anuQ7AwWrb3c"
          target="_blank"
          >What to Do If You Get Lost (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-11481">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 7. </span>
      Tell how to properly prepare for and deal with inclement weather. <br /><i
        >Resource:</i
      >
      <a href="https://youtu.be/J4atUCcf4p0?si=E5kHrCGO6P7evExq" target="_blank"
        >Backpacking in Rain, Lightning, Hail, and Wind (video)</a
      >
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-11482">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 8. </span>
      Do the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11482 mb-requirement-id-11483">
        (a) Explain the advantages and disadvantages of the different types of
        backpacking stoves using at least three different types of fuel.
        <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/DQdhvnXX8PM?si=-H_SQQdh77r70fb1"
          target="_blank"
          >Trying Every Type of Backpacking Stove! (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11482 mb-requirement-id-11484">
        (b) Demonstrate that you know how to operate a backpacking stove safely
        and to handle liquid fuel safely.
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11482 mb-requirement-id-11485">
        (c) Prepare three meals using a stove and fuel you can carry in a
        backpack.
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11482 mb-requirement-id-11486">
        (d) Demonstrate that you know how to keep cooking and eating gear clean
        and sanitary, and that you practice proper methods for food storage
        while on a backpacking trek. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/NNcu_Ujoiv4?si=ZZtSZLYJ73an86nj"
          target="_blank"
          >Clean-Up/Washing Dishes (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-11487">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 9. </span>
      Do the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11487 mb-requirement-id-11488">
        (a) Write a plan that includes a schedule for a patrol/crew backpacking
        hike of at least 2 miles. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/O1vtZSKr0pE?si=Uq1SBhiCqqT3OT_M"
          target="_blank"
          >How to Plan Your First Backpacking Trip (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11487 mb-requirement-id-11489">
        (b) Conduct a prehike inspection of the patrol and its equipment.
        <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/60iYJZoWBMA?si=uxYhraK_ZP3kNRAP"
          target="_blank"
          >Testing Your Backpacking Gear (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://nomadisbeautiful.com/travel-blogs/hiking-backpack-inspection-checklist/"
          target="_blank"
          >Hiking Backpack Inspection: The Ultimate Safety Checklist for Outdoor
          Enthusiasts (website)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11487 mb-requirement-id-11490">
        (c) Show that you know how to properly pack your personal gear and your
        share of the crew's gear and food. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/jBDido6uX9k?si=0eooOD1d3NvRP9Bb"
          target="_blank"
          >How to Pack Your Backpack (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11487 mb-requirement-id-11491">
        (d) Show you can properly shoulder your pack and adjust it for proper
        wear. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/0SGiGZlppMM?si=yf56DI_9Z9n7og8F"
          target="_blank"
          >How to Fit a Backpack (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11487 mb-requirement-id-11492">
        (e) While using the plan you developed for requirement 9(a), carry your
        fully loaded pack to complete a hike of at least 2 miles.
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-11493">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 10. </span>
      Following the Leave No Trace Seven Principles and the Outdoor Code,
      participate in at least three backpacking treks of at least three days
      each and at least 15 miles each, and using at least two different
      campsites on each trek. Carry everything you will need throughout the
      trek. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
      <a href="https://youtu.be/Rpq01rO9ZR0?si=hjjnThExBUjG0aIW" target="_blank"
        >What is Leave No trace? (video)</a
      ><br />
      <a href="https://lnt.org/why/7-principles/" target="_blank"
        >7 Principles - Leave No Trace (website)</a
      >
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-11494">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 11. </span>
      Do the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11494 mb-requirement-id-11495">
        (a) Write a plan for a backpacking trek of at least five days using at
        least three different campsites and covering at least 30 miles. Your
        plan must include a description of and route to the trek area, a
        schedule (including a daily schedule), a list of food and equipment
        needs, a safety and emergency plan, and a budget.
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11494 mb-requirement-id-11496">
        (b) Following the Leave No Trace Seven Principles and the Outdoor Code,
        take the trek as planned in requirement 11(a) that is at least five full
        days, covering at least 30 miles and utilizing at least three different
        campsites. While on trek, complete at least one service project approved
        by your counselor. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/Rpq01rO9ZR0?si=hjjnThExBUjG0aIW"
          target="_blank"
          >What is Leave No trace? (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://lnt.org/why/7-principles/" target="_blank"
          >7 Principles - Leave No Trace (website)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11494 mb-requirement-id-11497">
        (c) Keep a daily journal during the trek that includes a day-by-day
        description of your activities, including notes about what worked well
        and thoughts about improvements that could be made for the next trek.
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
</div>
